\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.3}{\ignorespaces The interior energy spectrum $E=\pm \sqrt  {p^2+m^2}$ (Proposition~\ref {prop:sea-spectrum}). The four positive-energy states are matter; the four negative-energy states, filled, are the Dirac sea. The chiral Hodge map $I$ exchanges the two branches by sending $m\DOTSB \mapstochar \rightarrow -m$ (Proposition~\ref {prop:sea-mirror}); since the branches are isospectral ($\omega ^2=p^2+m^2$), the negative-energy sector is a stable mirror, not a tachyon.}}{27}{figure.6.3}\protected@file@percent }
